title: Tooltip
description: a small popup showing descriptive text on hover or focus
---

{% from "components/tooltip/macro.njk" import tooltip %}
{% from "components/button/macro.njk" import button %}

<h2>Button with tooltip</h2>
<p>The controlling element references the tooltip's id via
  <code>aria-describedby</code>. Consumers reveal the tooltip on
  hover/focus via CSS or a JavaScript module.</p>

<p>
  {{ button({
    text: "Save",
    attributes: {
      "aria-describedby": "save-tooltip"
    }
  }) }}
  {{ tooltip({
    id: "save-tooltip",
    text: "Save the current draft. Press Ctrl+S.",
    hidden: false
  }) }}
</p>

<h2>Hidden by default</h2>
<p>Without overrides, a tooltip is rendered with the
  <code>hidden</code> attribute so it does not appear until
  progressive-enhancement JS toggles it.</p>

{{ tooltip({ id: "t2", text: "Invisible without JS enhancement" }) }}
<p>(The tooltip above is hidden — view source.)</p>
